The PEARL Awards Nigeria has officially announced that the 25th edition of the widely acknowledged prestigious Awards in the Nigerian Capital Market will take place later in the year. To this end, the Central Working Committee  (CWC) of the 2022 PEARL Awards was inaugurated last week Thursday.   JAMB releases 2022 UTME result     Adenuga, others, clinch National Productivity Awards     APC, PDP have lost touch with Nigerians, says NNPP Chairman   This according to the President, PEARL Awards, Mr. Tayo Orekoya kick-starts the official process and activities that culminates in the hosting of the Awards on the last Sunday of November each year. In his remarks, Orekoya said, the 2022 PEARL Awards with the theme: ‘Sustaining Excellence Through Tenacity (SETT),’ reflects the current realities of the PEARL Awards, our Corporates, and Capital Markets, locally and globally.